<subSubSection id="C368652E93528E0FF2AAFA59FCCFF9C2" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593528E0FF2AAFA59FCCFF9C2" blockId="11.[151,1437,1483,1725]" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">
<materialsCitation id="3B1A3CF893528E0FF2AAFA59FCCBF9C2" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798147310" collectorName="J. Serrano" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="lectotype">
The specimen here designated as 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793528E0FF032FA59FDA7FA2E" box="[527,630,1483,1509]" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">lectotype</typeStatus>
is a female bearing labels “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693528E0FF190FA59FBC4FA2F" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[941,1045,1483,1508]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acupalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriceps">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793528E0FF190FA59FBC4FA2F" box="[941,1045,1483,1508]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">nigriceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
m. in Gal. mer” and “ 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793528E0FF736FA59FAAFFA2E" box="[1291,1406,1483,1509]" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">Lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693528E0FF2AAFA7DFDC8F9C2" authority="Dejean, 1829" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[151,537,1519,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acupalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriceps">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793528E0FF2AAFA7DFEADF9C3" box="[151,380,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">Acupalpus nigriceps</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493528E0FF3B9FA7DFDC8F9C2" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[388,537,1519,1545]" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean, 1829</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
design. by 
<collectorName id="2687537393528E0FF0A7FA7DFCC1F9C2" box="[666,784,1519,1545]" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">J. Serrano</collectorName>
”
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C368652E93528E0FF2FAF981FD24F976" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593528E0FF2FAF981FBF5F9BF" blockId="11.[151,1437,1483,1725]" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">
The name is currently considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693528E0FF0D4F981FBAEF9E6" authority="(Sturm, 1825)" baseAuthorityName="Sturm" baseAuthorityYear="1825" box="[745,1151,1554,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acupalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicollis">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793528E0FF0D4F981FC04F9E6" box="[745,981,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">Acupalpus flavicollis</emphasis>
(Sturm, 1825)
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793528E0FF683F981FAF4F9E6" box="[1214,1317,1555,1581]" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">lectotype</typeStatus>
shows the characteristics of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693528E0FF366F9A5FD5BF99A" authority="(Sturm, 1825)" baseAuthorityName="Sturm" baseAuthorityYear="1825" box="[347,650,1590,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acupalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicollis">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793528E0FF366F9A5FE36F99A" box="[347,487,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">A. flavicollis</emphasis>
(Sturm, 1825)
</taxonomicName>
concerning most key characters (e.g., lack of dorsal pore in the second half of third interval of elytron) although dorsal coloration is somewhat different.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593528E0FF2FAF9EDFD24F976" blockId="11.[151,1437,1483,1725]" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">
As in the case of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693528E0FF3B3F9EDFE2FF952" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[398,510,1663,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acupalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luridus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793528E0FF3B3F9EDFE2FF952" box="[398,510,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">A. luridus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is difficult to understand why Dejean described it as a new species because he knew the 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793528E0FF339F931FEE5F976" box="[260,308,1699,1725]" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">type</typeStatus>
material of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693528E0FF381F931FD20F976" authority="(Sturm, 1825)" baseAuthorityName="Sturm" baseAuthorityYear="1825" box="[444,753,1698,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acupalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicollis">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793528E0FF381F931FD98F976" box="[444,585,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">A. flavicollis</emphasis>
(Sturm, 1825)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
